The paper discusses a new strategy for assessing partial dependence in machine learning models, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses issues related to codependent variables, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). The use of decision trees to stratify the data is a common technique in statistics (cs.ST) and machine learning (cs.LG), and the paper's focus on model interpretability is relevant to computational engineering (cs.CE).
